commit_message:
Don't override the policy files in the local settings

The setting override currently doesn't add anything (the file names are
kept the same) but causes new files added upstream to be missed as the
entire POLICY_FILES dictionary is being overriden.

Change-Id: I2ce4cace705e89ef2fbb4a2f4e57c9074fc512ac
Closes-Bug: #1296636

commit_message:
if log_file enabled, ensure log_dir is not absent

If log_file is specified, that means we should configure log_dir.
Otherwise, when running a command which use debug (like db-sync commands), it will try to write logs in the user directory which is not the best way.

This patch aims to ensure that we configure log_dir instead of remove
the flag like it was before.

Partial-bug #1292619
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

Change-Id: I94528b42a4865976f74d264facd91cb521c177bd

commit_message:
Only set port-range-min in icmp security rule

A change was merged recently Iebf109f246d47cffc26ab3c2cf113234a4b2cffe
That causes the icmp types being set in security rules to start taking
effect, before this they were ignored, we want to allow type 8 (ping)
adding it twice as in a range doesn't work.

Change-Id: Ie7bc9721ca41ee9d73343f07f24f0aa752911944
Closes-Bug: #1299022

There was introduced a new column vif_details for ml2_port_binding table
and dropped cap_port_filter column. Data was lost during the migration
causing no data in vif_details.

This patch transforms data from cap_port_filter to vif_details column as
a part of db migration. MigrationContext.execute() calls underlaying
methods depending whether migration is online or offline therefore data
are migrated in offline migration too.

Partial-bug: #1235149
Change-Id: Icc5dc6e8221a542f5190d0222ac4d10197d15ac1
'}]
commit_message:
Migrate data from cap_port_filter to vif_details

There was introduced a new column vif_details for ml2_port_binding table
and dropped cap_port_filter column. Data was lost during the migration
causing no data in vif_details.

This patch transforms data from cap_port_filter to vif_details column as
a part of db migration. MigrationContext.execute() calls underlaying
methods depending whether migration is online or offline therefore data
are migrated in offline migration too.

Partial-bug: #1235149
Change-Id: Icc5dc6e8221a542f5190d0222ac4d10197d15ac1

kvm package doesn't exist anymore in Debian since the Wheezy release.
It has been replace by qemu-kvm.
    http://packages.qa.debian.org/qemu
Please note this is also applicable for qemu Wheezy backports.

commit_message:
Debian: install the correct kvm package

kvm package doesn't exist anymore in Debian since the Wheezy release.
It has been replace by qemu-kvm.
    http://packages.qa.debian.org/qemu
Please note this is also applicable for qemu Wheezy backports.

This change adds the ability to use qemu-kvm when qemu is not available.

Change-Id: I16ae3f54f69e7509403363977d759ea215950e60

commit_message:
Move list stack method to SanityChecksTest class

When sanity stack tests inherits from heatmanager.Heat
class all object are initialized in setup.
So that we send flavor creation request in sanity
list stack tests.
Move list_stack function to the SanityChecksTest class
to avoid post operation and object creation in sanity suit

Change-Id: Ie7c3d7ab9c29d455e42126e37ac9e3ec71fdc26c
Closes-bug: #1297360

commit_message:
Correct multi-line neutron attribute detection

The way that arrays were built-up for multi-line items caused the arrays
to become more tested with each element, making structures like
[[[a, b], c], d]

This corrects the behavior

Change-Id: I045abdfefd6f2cc85d0d9c70d3375fdce302f05d

This change converts calling into address_for to resolve the IP to
bind the VNC server to into a call into an endpoint.  This allows the

Change-Id: I956695c473e2cd7ada8da3d4249204b86e148b71

commit_message:
Converted VNC service IP binding to endpoint

This change converts calling into address_for to resolve the IP to
bind the VNC server to into a call into an endpoint.  This allows the
user to either specify an interface or an IP to bind to using the
standard endpoint library.

This change is dependent on change: https://review.openstack.org/83440

blueprint increase-ip-binding-flexibility

Change-Id: I956695c473e2cd7ada8da3d4249204b86e148b71

commit_message:
Include cisco plugin in migration plugins with ovs

Currently we have many migration files with missing cisco
plugin in migrate_plugin when ovs is included.This
causes missing tables when cisco plugin is enabled
and migration is run. This fix should automatically
include the cisco plugin if ovs is detected in the
migrate_plugins.

Change-Id: I4dedfbafe9b431e85255d5427766e22eed09ee5e
Closes-Bug: #1292114

commit_message:
De-dupe selectable aggregate list in statistics API

Fixes bug 1298514

Discard full duplicates from the selectable aggregate list passed
to the statistics API.

Partial duplicates (i.e. matching func but different param) are
now allowed and supported by the storage drivers.

Change-Id: I5e2780befa9e265d5f1deb71b2aa375d05ca2e64

Moved firewall section and restructured Compute section

Renamed log-file chapter to match other 'file' chapter.
Moved Compute sections into files to trim down the massive
Compute chapter file. Edited touched files.

Previously, subnet had some parameters as read-only which blocks some

Improve Neutron subnets management

Previously, subnet had some parameters as read-only which blocks some
features, like specifing dns servers, allocation pools and also specific
host routes. This patch aims to add support for these options as well for creation
and also for update (for some of them where API allows it).

commit_message:
1284343 RouterNotFound not handled correctly.

Unfortunately, at the current time, neutronclient does not have a
RouterNotFound exception (unlike NetworkNotFound or PortNotFound).
Instead, a NeutronClientException is thrown, which needs to be converted
into a type of exception that horizon.exceptions.handle believes to be a
NOT_FOUND exception.

NOTE:  This is a temporary solution that should be removed once the
       neutron client is fixed.

Change-Id: I27b3e600455b7bfc68d0207369f64bb1d10c4dfc
Closes-Bug: 1284343

commit_message:
Remove escape character in string format

String format can use escape character '\' to break lines, but it
requires the continuous line not be aligned or the spaces will be
included too. This patch uses parentheses to format string, and
removes the '\'.

Change-Id: I6c007d48d9b99d102c82b4d93ef6f825828e9e20

* Added ObjectNotFound and ObjectNotUnique exception for database entities
* Renamed previous NotFound exception in ResourceNotFound

glued to the API: before this change, _raise_not_found
couldn't be used  with sqlalchemy objects that are not associated to
any API resource, Indeed these objects don't have a __resource__
defined and _raise_not_found needed this field.
* Applied the same behavior to ResourceExists and then also created
ObjectNotUnique specific exception to database entities.

Change-Id: I6ff7d90562e4f03ecaf7cea52d03cc46caee51c3
"}]
commit_message:
Fix SolumBase _raise_not_found() 'glued' to the API due to __resource__

* Added ObjectNotFound and ObjectNotUnique exception for database entities
* Renamed previous NotFound exception in ResourceNotFound
* _raise_not_found() in SolumBase (sqlalchemy base class) is not anymore
glued to the API: before this change, _raise_not_found
couldn't be used  with sqlalchemy objects that are not associated to
any API resource, Indeed these objects don't have a __resource__
defined and _raise_not_found needed this field.
* Applied the same behavior to ResourceExists and then also created
ObjectNotUnique specific exception to database entities.

Change-Id: I6ff7d90562e4f03ecaf7cea52d03cc46caee51c3

commit_message:
Documenting hypervisor support for nova meters

Support was recently added for HyperV and Vsphere for Nova meters in
ceilometer. However, not all meters are supported by all the
hypervisors. Hence, have added documentation to list the meters and the
hypervisors which provide support for them.

commit_message:
Skip volume snapshot tests if feature is not enabled

Not all cinder volume backends support volume snapshot. For instance,
the default NFS backend doesn't. This patch adds a new entry to
CONF.volume_feature_enabled to add the possibility to skip volume
snapshot tests.

Change-Id: I40ce17924bbe4eb6f1c941df974bfa832ec2a999

commit_message:
Null-override yum/apt providers and package type (puppet 3.4.2)

This is just a 'nullchange override'.
We just put vanilla versions for puppet 3.4.2 yum, apt providers
and package type, so we could track its versioning history here.
These are will be overrided for patching openstack needs later.

Partial-blueprint: patch-openstack

commit_message:
Add new overcloud all-in-one template.

Useful when you want to test an all in one overcloud due to
limited resources (bare metal, or memory). We may also
want to make use of self contained overclouds for some
CI related tasks as well.

Change-Id: I743e828f162a57a84de5a9b06b4947f08fa2b317
